const bodyHtml = "<main><div class=\"site-shell article-layout\"><article class=\"article\"><a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-04-06 • Bazaar Flipping</a><h1>NPC to Bazaar Flips in Hypixel SkyBlock</h1><p class=\"lede\">NPC-to-bazaar flips are some of the least glamorous money routes in the game, which is part of why they survive. They live in the gap between fixed NPC pricing and player convenience, and they stay profitable because most players would rather ignore them than optimize them. Current flipping coverage treats these routes as foundational market literacy: they teach you to respect boring profit, daily limits and the difference between a stable route and an exciting but unreliable one.</p><div class=\"note\"><strong>Primary source base:</strong> current bazaar and reverse-NPC tool research across SkyCofl, Skyblock.bz and BazaarTracker, combined with creator advice on stable low-complexity flips.</div><h2>Boring routes are often durable routes</h2><p>The appeal of NPC-to-bazaar flips is not that they create huge per-trade margins. The appeal is that the logic is clean. If players still pay the bazaar price for an item obtainable at an NPC, and daily caps or inconvenience keep the route from being farmed to zero, the flip can stay alive much longer than flashy content-driven strategies. That is exactly why these routes deserve a place in a guide library aimed at long-term search traffic: new players underestimate them and advanced players often skip writing about them.</p><p>The best way to approach the method is as a discipline test. Can you accept smaller but cleaner wins? Can you check caps, transport time and exit liquidity without getting bored? Players who can do that often end up with steadier income than players constantly jumping to the newest screenshot-friendly margin.</p><h2>Use reverse-NPC tools, then apply judgment</h2><p><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar/npcresell\">SkyCofl reverse NPC</a>, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/reverse_npc\">Skyblock.bz reverse-NPC feed</a>, <a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/npc-mayor-flips\">BazaarPro NPC &amp; mayor flips</a> and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/npc\">BazaarTracker NPC routes</a> are the discovery layer. Each one ranks routes by real-time spread, instant-sell volume and modifier-aware ROI. Discovery is still only step one. You need to think about daily caps, travel friction and whether the bazaar side is deep enough to absorb your size at median price without collapsing the route. These flips look simple because the buy side is simple. The sell side is where discipline still matters.</p><p>That combination of simple entry and modest edge makes NPC-to-bazaar flips especially good for early and midgame players. They are rarely the fastest route to wealth, but they are one of the clearest ways to learn how market convenience creates value.</p><h2>Read next</h2><ul class=\"related-list\"><li><a href=\"/guides/passive-bazaar-orders-guide\">Passive Bazaar Orders Guide</a></li><li><a href=\"/guides/bazaar-flipping-guide-2026\">Bazaar Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li><li><a href=\"/guides/first-50m-coins-guide\">Your First 50M Coins in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li></ul></article><aside class=\"article-aside\"><div><h3>Best paired tools</h3><ul class=\"tool-list\"><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar/npcresell\">SkyCofl reverse NPC</a></li><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/npc\">SkyCofl NPC flips</a></li><li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/reverse_npc\">Skyblock.bz reverse NPC</a></li><li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/npc\">Skyblock.bz NPC flips</a></li><li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/npc-mayor-flips\">BazaarPro NPC &amp; mayor flips</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/npc\">BazaarTracker NPC</a></li></ul></div><div><h3>Best for</h3><p>Players who want reliable low-complexity flips and are willing to trade excitement for cleaner logic.</p></div><div><h3>Source videos</h3><p>This page leans more heavily on live tool behavior because reverse-NPC routes are best read as ongoing market structure rather than one creator's temporary route.</p></div></aside></div></main>";
